{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775838240349,"sessionID":"ses_287cb09c2ffefSoaqLWDpvusWV","part":{"id":"prt_d783519f6001p7sSUPjtIi5zgj","messageID":"msg_d78350ea9001aSGzA3fc3lUbzn","sessionID":"ses_287cb09c2ffefSoaqLWDpvusWV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_4def41ebf5534a5d965e43d3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/store\n4: **Language:** Go\n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: AR-012 定义了 Session Store 的接口，AR-013 完成了 Redis 后端实现。当前 `pkg/store` 缺少 Valkey 后端实现，无法为使用 Valkey 作为缓存层的部署场景提供 session 存储能力。\n10: \n11: Valkey 是 Redis 的开源替代品，协议兼容但使用不同的 Go 客户端库（`github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`）。本 AR 实现与 Redis 后端同等能力的 `valkeyStore`，确保部署时可通过 `STORE_TYPE=valkey` 切换后端，满足使用 Valkey 集群的 Kubernetes 部署需求。\n12: \n13: ## Proposed Solution\n14: \n15: 实现 `valkeyStore` 结构体，使用 `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` 客户端库，提供与 `redisStore` 相同的功能：\n16: \n17: 1. **Valkey 数据模型** — 与 Redis 相同的 key 模式和数据结构（String + Sorted Set）\n18: 2. **CRUD 操作** — `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`\n19: 3. **查询操作** — `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes` 使用 `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs`（MGET 批量加载）\n20: 4. **辅助操作** — `Ping`, `Close`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`\n21: 5. **构造函数** — 环境变量验证（`VALKEY_ADDR`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED`, `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE`, `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE`）\n22: \n23: ## Scope\n24: \n25: ### In Scope\n26: \n27: 1. **Valkey 实现**（`store_valkey.go`）\n28:    - `valkeyStore` 结构体与 `Store` 接口完整实现\n29:    - 构造函数 `newValkeyStore() (*valkeyStore, error)`\n30:    - 所有 CRUD、查询、辅助方法\n31: \n32: 2. **Valkey 单元测试**（`store_valkey_test.go`）\n33:    - 与 Redis 测试用例对等的完整测试矩阵\n34:    - 覆盖 spec 中全部 scenario\n35: \n36: 3. **Singleton 集成**（`singleton.go`）\n37:    - `STORE_TYPE=valkey` 时选择 Valkey 后端\n38: \n39: ### Out of Scope\n40: \n41: - Redis 后端变更（AR-013 已覆盖）\n42: - 调用方组件适配（由各自 AR 覆盖）\n43: - Helm Chart 或部署配置变更\n44: - Valkey 集群模式 hash slot 问题（代码注释说明即可）\n45: \n46: ## Impact Analysis\n47: \n48: ### Files Modified\n49: \n50: | File | Change |\n51: |------|--------|\n52: | `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | 新建 — `valkeyStore` 完整实现 |\n53: | `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go` | 新建 — 单元测试 |\n54: | `pkg/store/singleton.go` | 新增 `valkeyStoreType` 常量匹配分支 |\n55: | `go.mod` / `go.sum` | 新增 `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` 依赖 |\n56: \n57: ### Dependencies\n58: \n59: | 依赖 | 状态 | 说明 |\n60: |------|------|------|\n61: | AR-012（会话存储接口定义） | 已完成 | 提供了 Store 接口 |\n62: | AR-013（Redis 存储实现） | 已完成 | 参考实现与测试模式 |\n63: | `pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo` | 已存在 | 数据模型 |\n64: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | 待引入 | Valkey 客户端依赖 |\n65: \n66: ### Backward Compatibility\n67: \n68: - `STORE_TYPE` 默认值仍为 `redis`，无行为变更\n69: - `Store` 接口不变，Valkey 实现满足同一契约\n70: - 现有 Redis 用户不受影响\n71: \n72: ### Risk Assessment\n73: \n74: | 风险 | 等级 | 缓解措施 |\n75: |------|------|----------|\n76: | Valkey 客户端 API 与 Redis 不完全兼容 | 中 | 对照 valkey-go 文档逐方法验证；参考 AR-013 设计模式 |\n77: | Valkey MGET 跨 hash slot 失败（集群模式） | 中 | 代码注释说明 key 需落在同一 slot；建议使用 hash tag |\n78: | 测试依赖 Valkey 实例 | 低 | 使用 valkey-go 的 mock 或兼容测试工具 |\n79: \n80: ### 与现有组件的交互\n81: \n82: | 组件 | 交互方式 | 影响 |\n83: |------|----------|------|\n84: | Session Store 接口 | 实现同一 `Store` interface | 无影响，多态替换 |\n85: | Redis 实现 | 并行存在，运行时二选一 | 无影响 |\n86: | Singleton (`Storage()`) | 新增 `valkey` 分支 | 无影响，`sync.Once` 保证单次初始化 |\n87: | client-go | 生成的 K8s 客户端库 | 无影响，store 包不依赖 K8s API |\n88: \n89: ## Alternatives Considered\n90: \n91: ### 1. 复用 go-redis 客户端连接 Valkey（❌ 不采用）\n92: \n93: **做法**：Valkey 兼容 Redis 协议，使用已有的 `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` 直接连接 Valkey 实例。\n94: \n95: **优点**：\n96: - 零新增依赖\n97: - 代码复用度高，与 Redis 实现共享大部分逻辑\n98: \n99: **缺点**：\n100: - 无法利用 Valkey 专有特性（RESP3 原生支持、pipeline 性能优化）\n101: - 版本升级路径受限，Valkey 协议演进可能产生兼容性问题\n102: - 无法针对 Valkey 集群模式做专门优化\n103: \n104: **决策**：不采用。专用客户端提供更好的性能和未来可扩展性。\n105: \n106: ### 2. 统一抽象层（Redis/Valkey 共享基类）（❌ 不采用）\n107: \n108: **做法**：提取 Redis 和 Valkey 的共性到一个共享基类或组合结构，减少代码重复。\n109: \n110: **优点**：\n111: - 减少代码重复\n112: - 统一错误处理路径\n113: \n114: **缺点**：\n115: - 两客户端 API 差异大（go-redis 的 `Pipeline` vs valkey-go 的 `DoMulti`/`B().Cmd()`）\n116: - 强行抽象会增加复杂度，降低可读性\n117: - 后续任一客户端升级都需要修改共享层\n118: \n119: **决策**：不采用。当前设计采用各自独立 struct 实现同一 `Store` 接口，保持实现清晰。\n120: \n121: ### 3. 专用 Valkey 客户端（✅ 选定方案）\n122: \n123: **做法**：使用 `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` 实现独立的 `valkeyStore`，与 `redisStore` 并行。\n124: \n125: **优点**：\n126: - 充分利用 Valkey 客户端特性（RESP3、pipeline 性能）\n127: - 实现独立，互不影响\n128: - 符合当前 singleton 模式，运行时通过 `STORE_TYPE` 切换\n129: \n130: **缺点**：\n131: - 新增依赖\n132: - 两份实现需要分别维护\n133: \n134: **决策**：采用。与现有架构最契合，变更范围可控（S 级）。\n135: \n136: ### 4. 通过 build tag 选择后端（❌ 不采用）\n137: \n138: **做法**：使用编译时 build tag 决定使用 Redis 或 Valkey 实现。\n139: \n140: **优点**：\n141: - 编译产物更小（只包含一个后端）\n142: - 无运行时选择开销\n143: \n144: **缺点**：\n145: - 同一镜像无法支持两种后端\n146: - 部署灵活性差，需要分别构建\n147: - 与当前运行时 `STORE_TYPE` 环境变量设计不符\n148: \n149: **决策**：不采用。运行时选择更符合 AgentCube 的部署模型。\n150: \n151: ## Implementation Notes\n152: \n153: ### valkeyStore 结构体\n154: \n155: ```go\n156: type valkeyStore struct {\n157:     cli                  valkey.Client\n158:     sessionPrefix        string\n159:     expiryIndexKey       string\n160:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n161: }\n162: ```\n163: \n164: 常量与 Redis 实现一致：\n165: - `sessionPrefix = \"session:\"`\n166: - `expiryIndexKey = \"session:expiry\"`\n167: - `lastActivityIndexKey = \"session:last_activity\"`\n168: \n169: ### 环境变量\n170: \n171: | Variable | Required | Notes |\n172: |----------|----------|-------|\n173: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | 逗号分隔地址列表 → `InitAddress` |\n174: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | |\n175: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `\"true\"` 时设置 `DisableCache` |\n176: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `\"true\"` 时设置 `ForceSingleClient` |\n177: | `STORE_TYPE` | Must be `valkey` | 大小写不敏感 |\n178: \n179: ### 方法映射\n180: \n181: | Method | Valkey API |\n182: |--------|------------|\n183: | `Ping` | `B().Ping()` → 校验 `PONG` |\n184: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `B().Get().Key(key)` → `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n185: | `StoreSandbox` | `DoMulti`：`SETNX` + `ZADD` expiry + `ZADD` last_activity |\n186: | `UpdateSandbox` | `B().Set().Key().Value().Xx()` → 校验 `ToString() == \"OK\"` |\n187: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `DoMulti`：`DEL` + `ZREM` expiry + `ZREM` last_activity |\n188: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `Zrangebyscore` Min(`-inf`) Max(`before.Unix`) Limit |\n189: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | 同上，目标 key 为 `last_activity` |\n190: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `Exists` key → `Zadd` |\n191: | `Close` | `cli.Close()` |\n192: \n193: ### ZSET Score 语义\n194: \n195: - **Expiry index:** score = `float64(sandboxRedis.ExpiresAt.Unix())` on store\n196: - **Last activity:** score = `float64(time.Now().Unix())` on `StoreSandbox`；`float64(at.Unix())` on `UpdateSessionLastActivity`\n197: \n198: ### MGET 注意\n199: \n200: `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` 使用单 `Mget` 批量加载所有 `session:{id}` keys。代码需注释说明：集群模式下这些 key 需落在同一 hash slot。\n201: \n202: ### Singleton 集成\n203: \n204: 在 `initStore()` 中新增：\n205: ```go\n206: case valkeyStoreType:\n207:     provider, err = newValkeyStore()\n208: ```\n209: \n210: ## Acceptance Criteria\n211: \n212: 1. **接口实现**\n213:    - [ ] `valkeyStore` 完整实现 `Store` 接口所有方法\n214:    - [ ] `STORE_TYPE=valkey` 时 `Storage()` 返回 `*valkeyStore`\n215: \n216: 2. **Spec 合规**\n217:    - [ ] 所有 spec scenario 验证通过（Ping、NotFound、Key naming、Expiry index、Last-activity index、StoreSandbox atomicity、UpdateSandbox semantics、Delete cleanup、List loaders tolerance、UpdateSessionLastActivity preconditions、Provider selection、Password policy、Singleton access）\n218: \n219: 3. **测试覆盖**\n220:    - [ ] 单元测试覆盖所有方法及边界场景\n221:    - [ ] 与 Redis 测试用例对等\n222: \n223: 4. **代码质量**\n224:    - [ ] `go vet ./pkg/store/...` 无告警\n225:    - [ ] `go mod tidy` 后无未使用依赖\n226: \n227: ## Status\n228: \n229: - [ ] 提案审查\n230: - [ ] 实现\n231: - [ ] 验证\n\n(End of file - total 231 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\n\n**Module:** pkg/store\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** S\n\n## Purpose\n\nAR-012 定义了 Session Store 的接口，AR-013 完成了 Redis 后端实现。当前 `pkg/store` 缺少 Valkey 后端实现，无法为使用 Valkey 作为缓存层的部署场景提供 session 存储能力。\n\nValkey 是 Redis 的开源替代品，协议兼容但使用不同的 Go 客户端库（`github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`）。本 AR 实现与 Redis 后端同等能力的 `valkeyStore`，确保部署时可通过 `STORE_TYPE=valkey` 切换后端，满足使用 Valkey 集群的 Kubernetes 部署需求。\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\n实现 `valkeyStore` 结构体，使用 `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` 客户端库，提供与 `redisStore` 相同的功能：\n\n1. **Valkey 数据模型** — 与 Redis 相同的 key 模式和数据结构（String + Sorted Set）\n2. **CRUD 操作** — `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`\n3. **查询操作** — `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes` 使用 `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs`（MGET 批量加载）\n4. **辅助操作** — `Ping`, `Close`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775838240330,"end":1775838240347}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775838241712,"sessionID":"ses_287cb09c2ffefSoaqLWDpvusWV","part":{"id":"prt_d78351edc0015U8MyVwjV6j4q2","messageID":"msg_d78350ea9001aSGzA3fc3lUbzn","sessionID":"ses_287cb09c2ffefSoaqLWDpvusWV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3436f456d3cd4c4a91d1dc4f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014 — Valkey Storage Implementation — Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: This document specifies the Valkey backend implementation for the `pkg/store` session storage module in AgentCube. It provides a concrete `Store` interface implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`, persisting sandbox metadata as JSON strings and maintaining sorted-set indices for garbage collection workflows.\n8: \n9: ### 1.2 Valkey Data Architecture\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n13: │                    valkeyStore                          │\n14: │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n15: │  │  cli: valkey.Client                               │  │\n16: │  │  sessionPrefix:        \"session:\"                 │  │\n17: │  │  expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\"           │  │\n18: │  │  lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\"    │  │\n19: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n20: └───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────┘\n21:                         │\n22:                         ▼\n23: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n24: │                      Valkey Server                      │\n25: │                                                         │\n26: │  String Keys:                                           │\n27: │    session:{sessionID} → JSON(SandboxInfo)              │\n28: │                                                         │\n29: │  Sorted Sets:                                           │\n30: │    session:expiry          ZSET { sessionID: score }    │\n31: │      score = ExpiresAt.Unix()                           │\n32: │                                                         │\n33: │    session:last_activity   ZSET { sessionID: score }    │\n34: │      score = time.Now().Unix() (on store)               │\n35: │                                                         │\n36: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ### 1.3 Package Layout\n40: \n41: ```\n42: pkg/store/\n43: ├── store.go                  # Store interface (shared)\n44: ├── singleton.go              # Provider selection (shared)\n45: ├── store_valkey.go           # Valkey implementation ← AR-014\n46: ├── store_valkey_test.go      # Valkey unit tests ← AR-014\n47: └── codec.go                  # JSON encode/decode helpers (shared)\n48: ```\n49: \n50: ### 1.4 Dependencies\n51: \n52: | Module | Version | Purpose |\n53: |--------|---------|---------|\n54: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | latest | Valkey client library |\n55: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | — | `SandboxInfo` type alias |\n56: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/handler` | — | `SandboxInfo` struct definition |\n57: \n58: ---\n59: \n60: ## 2. Data Model\n61: \n62: ### 2.1 Valkey Store Struct\n63: \n64: ```go\n65: type valkeyStore struct {\n66:     cli                  valkey.Client\n67:     sessionPrefix        string\n68:     expiryIndexKey       string\n69:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n70: }\n71: ```\n72: \n73: ### 2.2 Key Constants\n74: \n75: | Constant | Value | Purpose |\n76: |----------|-------|---------|\n77: | `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` | Prefix for session JSON string keys |\n78: | `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` | ZSET for expiry-based GC queries |\n79: | `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` | ZSET for activity-based GC queries |\n80: \n81: ### 2.3 Valkey Key Patterns\n82: \n83: | Key Pattern | Type | Content |\n84: |-------------|------|---------|\n85: | `session:{sessionID}` | String | JSON-marshaled `SandboxInfo` |\n86: | `session:expiry` | Sorted Set | Member: `sessionID`, Score: `ExpiresAt.Unix()` |\n87: | `session:last_activity` | Sorted Set | Member: `sessionID`, Score: `time.Now().Unix()` |\n88: \n89: ### 2.4 SandboxInfo JSON Schema\n90: \n91: Stored as JSON string at `session:{sessionID}`:\n92: \n93: ```json\n94: {\n95:   \"sessionId\": \"session-abc-123\",\n96:   \"sandboxName\": \"sandbox-name\",\n97:   \"sandboxId\": \"uuid-string\",\n98:   \"workloadName\": \"agent-runtime\",\n99:   \"namespace\": \"default\",\n100:   \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n101:   \"podIp\": \"10.0.0.1\",\n102:   \"entryPoints\": [\n103:     {\n104:       \"path\": \"/api\",\n105:       \"protocol\": \"http\",\n106:       \"endpoint\": \"http://10.0.0.1:8080\"\n107:     }\n108:   ],\n109:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-10T07:00:00Z\",\n110:   \"expiresAt\": \"2026-04-10T08:00:00Z\",\n111:   \"status\": \"running\",\n112:   \"lastActivityAt\": \"2026-04-10T07:05:00Z\"\n113: }\n114: ```\n115: \n116: ### 2.5 Sorted Set Score Semantics\n117: \n118: | Index | Score Source | When Written |\n119: |-------|-------------|--------------|\n120: | `session:expiry` | `float64(ExpiresAt.Unix())` | `StoreSandbox` |\n121: | `session:last_activity` | `float64(time.Now().Unix())` | `StoreSandbox` |\n122: | `session:last_activity` | `float64(at.Unix())` or `time.Now()` | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` |\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## 3. Interfaces\n127: \n128: ### 3.1 Store Interface\n129: \n130: `valkeyStore` implements the shared `Store` interface defined in `store.go`:\n131: \n132: ```go\n133: type Store interface {\n134:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n135:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n136:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n137:     GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n138:     ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) (map[string]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n139:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n140:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n141:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n142:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n143:     Close() error\n144: }\n145: ```\n146: \n147: ### 3.2 Method Specifications\n148: \n149: #### 3.2.1 Ping\n150: \n151: | Aspect | Detail |\n152: |--------|--------|\n153: | Valkey Command | `B().Ping().Build()` via `Do()` |\n154: | Success | Response string equals `\"PONG\"` |\n155: | Error | Connection error propagated |\n156: \n157: ```go\n158: func (v *valkeyStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error {\n159:     resp, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Ping().Build()).ToString()\n160:     if err != nil {\n161:         return err\n162:     }\n163:     if resp != \"PONG\" {\n164:         return fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected ping response: %s\", resp)\n165:     }\n166:     return nil\n167: }\n168: ```\n169: \n170: #### 3.2.2 GetSandbox\n171: \n172: | Aspect | Detail |\n173: |--------|--------|\n174: | Key | `session:{sessionID}` |\n175: | Valkey Command | `B().Get().Key(key).Build()` |\n176: | Not Found | `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` → `ErrNotFound` |\n177: | Success | JSON unmarshal via `decodeSandboxInfo()` |\n178: \n179: ```go\n180: func (v *valkeyStore) GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n181:     key := v.sessionKey(sessionID)\n182:     data, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Get().Key(key).Build()).ToString()\n183:     if valkey.IsValkeyNil(err) {\n184:         return nil, ErrNotFound\n185:     }\n186:     if err != nil {\n187:         return nil, err\n188:     }\n189:     return decodeSandboxInfo([]byte(data))\n190: }\n191: ```\n192: \n193: #### 3.2.3 StoreSandbox\n194: \n195: | Aspect | Detail |\n196: |--------|--------|\n197: | Validation | Reject nil sandbox; reject zero `ExpiresAt` |\n198: | Valkey Commands | `DoMulti`: `SETNX`, `ZADD` (expiry), `ZADD` (activity) |\n199: | Atomicity | Commands sent in single `DoMulti` call; each result checked for errors |\n200: | Idempotency | `SETNX` prevents overwriting existing session |\n201: \n202: ```go\n203: func (v *valkeyStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n204:     if info == nil {\n205:         return errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")\n206:     }\n207:     if info.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n208:         return errors.New(\"sandbox ExpiresAt is zero\")\n209:     }\n210: \n211:     data, err := encodeSandboxInfo(info)\n212:     if err != nil {\n213:         return fmt.Errorf(\"marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n214:     }\n215: \n216:     key := v.sessionKey(sessionID)\n217:     now := float64(time.Now().Unix())\n218:     expiryScore := float64(info.ExpiresAt.Unix())\n219: \n220:     results := v.cli.DoMulti(ctx,\n221:         v.cli.B().Setnx().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Build(),\n222:         v.cli.B().Zadd().Key(v.expiryIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(expiryScore, sessionID).Build(),\n223:         v.cli.B().Zadd().Key(v.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(now, sessionID).Build(),\n224:     )\n225: \n226:     for _, result := range results {\n227:         if err := result.Error(); err != nil {\n228:             return err\n229:         }\n230:     }\n231:     return nil\n232: }\n233: ```\n234: \n235: #### 3.2.4 UpdateSandbox\n236: \n237: | Aspect | Detail |\n238: |--------|--------|\n239: | Valkey Command | `B().Set().Key(key).Value(data).Xx().Build()` |\n240: | Not Found | Response != `\"OK\"` → `fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists: %s\", key)` |\n241: | Side Effects | Does NOT modify ZSET entries |\n242: \n243: ```go\n244: func (v *valkeyStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n245:     if info == nil {\n246:         return errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")\n247:     }\n248: \n249:     data, err := encodeSandboxInfo(info)\n250:     if err != nil {\n251:         return fmt.Errorf(\"marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n252:     }\n253: \n254:     key := v.sessionKey(sessionID)\n255:     resp, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Xx().Build()).ToString()\n256:     if err != nil {\n257:         return err\n258:     }\n259:     if resp != \"OK\" {\n260:         return fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists: %s\", key)\n261:     }\n262:     return nil\n263: }\n264: ```\n265: \n266: #### 3.2.5 DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n267: \n268: | Aspect | Detail |\n269: |--------|--------|\n270: | Valkey Commands | `DoMulti`: `DEL`, `ZREM` (expiry), `ZREM` (activity) |\n271: | Atomicity | All commands in single `DoMulti` call |\n272: \n273: ```go\n274: func (v *valkeyStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n275:     results := v.cli.DoMulti(ctx,\n276:         v.cli.B().Del().Key(v.sessionPrefix+sessionID).Build(),\n277:         v.cli.B().Zrem().Key(v.expiryIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build(),\n278:         v.cli.B().Zrem().Key(v.lastActivityIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build(),\n279:     )\n280: \n281:     for _, result := range results {\n282:         if err := result.Error(); err != nil {\n283:             return err\n284:         }\n285:     }\n286:     return nil\n287: }\n288: ```\n289: \n290: #### 3.2.6 ListSandboxes\n291: \n292: | Aspect | Detail |\n293: |--------|--------|\n294: | Valkey Command | `B().Zrange().Key(expiryIndexKey).Min(\"0\").Max(\"-1\").Build()` |\n295: | Follow-up | Individual `GetSandbox` calls per session ID |\n296: | Missing Keys | Orphan ZSET members skipped (not errors) |\n297: | Return Type | `map[string]*types.SandboxInfo` keyed by session ID |\n298: \n299: ```go\n300: func (v *valkeyStore) ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) (map[string]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n301:     sessionIDs, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Zrange().Key(v.expiryIndexKey).Min(\"0\").Max(\"-1\").Build()).AsStrSlice()\n302:     if err != nil {\n303:         return nil, err\n304:     }\n305: \n306:     result := make(map[string]*types.SandboxInfo)\n307:     for _, id := range sessionIDs {\n308:         info, err := v.GetSandbox(ctx, id)\n309:         if err != nil {\n310:             if err == ErrNotFound {\n311:                 continue\n312:             }\n313:             return nil, err\n314:         }\n315:         result[id] = info\n316:     }\n317: \n318:     return result, nil\n319: }\n320: ```\n321: \n322: #### 3.2.7 ListExpiredSandboxes\n323: \n324: | Aspect | Detail |\n325: |--------|--------|\n326: | Precondition | `limit <= 0` → return `nil, nil` |\n327: | Valkey Command | `B().Zrangebyscore().Key(expiryIndexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(maxScore).Limit(0, limit).Build()` |\n328: | Follow-up | Individual `GetSandbox` calls per session ID |\n329: | Missing Keys | Orphan ZSET members skipped |\n330: | Return Type | `[]*types.SandboxInfo` slice |\n331: \n332: ```go\n333: func (v *valkeyStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n334:     if limit <= 0 {\n335:         return nil, nil\n336:     }\n337: \n338:     maxScore := strconv.FormatInt(before.Unix(), 10)\n339:     sessionIDs, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Zrangebyscore().Key(v.expiryIndexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(maxScore).Limit(0, int64(limit)).Build()).AsStrSlice()\n340:     if err != nil {\n341:         return nil, err\n342:     }\n343: \n344:     var result []*types.SandboxInfo\n345:     for _, id := range sessionIDs {\n346:         info, err := v.GetSandbox(ctx, id)\n347:         if err != nil {\n348:             if err == ErrNotFound {\n349:                 continue\n350:             }\n351:             return nil, err\n352:         }\n353:         result = append(result, info)\n354:     }\n355: \n356:     return result, nil\n357: }\n358: ```\n359: \n360: #### 3.2.8 ListInactiveSandboxes\n361: \n362: | Aspect | Detail |\n363: |--------|--------|\n364: | Same as ListExpiredSandboxes | Queries `session:last_activity` ZSET |\n365: \n366: ```go\n367: func (v *valkeyStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n368:     if limit <= 0 {\n369:         return nil, nil\n370:     }\n371: \n372:     maxScore := strconv.FormatInt(before.Unix(), 10)\n373:     sessionIDs, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Zrangebyscore().Key(v.lastActivityIndexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(maxScore).Limit(0, int64(limit)).Build()).AsStrSlice()\n374:     if err != nil {\n375:         return nil, err\n376:     }\n377: \n378:     var result []*types.SandboxInfo\n379:     for _, id := range sessionIDs {\n380:         info, err := v.GetSandbox(ctx, id)\n381:         if err != nil {\n382:             if err == ErrNotFound {\n383:                 continue\n384:             }\n385:             return nil, err\n386:         }\n387:         result = append(result, info)\n388:     }\n389: \n390:     return result, nil\n391: }\n392: ```\n393: \n394: #### 3.2.9 UpdateSessionLastActivity\n395: \n396: | Aspect | Detail |\n397: |--------|--------|\n398: | Validation | Reject empty `sessionID` |\n399: | Zero Time | If `at.IsZero()`, use `time.Now()` |\n400: | Precondition | Session key must exist; absent → `ErrNotFound` |\n401: | Valkey Commands | `EXISTS` → `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n402: \n403: ```go\n404: func (v *valkeyStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error {\n405:     if sessionID == \"\" {\n406:         return errors.New(\"sessionID is empty\")\n407:     }\n408: \n409:     if at.IsZero() {\n410:         at = time.Now()\n411:     }\n412: \n413:     key := v.sessionKey(sessionID)\n414:     exists, err := v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Exists().Key(key).Build()).AsInt64()\n415:     if err != nil {\n416:         return err\n417:     }\n418:     if exists == 0 {\n419:         return ErrNotFound\n420:     }\n421: \n422:     score := float64(at.Unix())\n423:     return v.cli.Do(ctx, v.cli.B().Zadd().Key(v.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(score, sessionID).Build()).Error()\n424: }\n425: ```\n426: \n427: #### 3.2.10 Close\n428: \n429: ```go\n430: func (v *valkeyStore) Close() error {\n431:     v.cli.Close()\n432:     return nil\n433: }\n434: ```\n435: \n436: ### 3.3 Helper Functions\n437: \n438: #### 3.3.1 sessionKey\n439: \n440: ```go\n441: func (v *valkeyStore) sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n442:     return v.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n443: }\n444: ```\n445: \n446: ### 3.4 Constructor\n447: \n448: ```go\n449: func newValkeyStore() (Store, error) {\n450:     addr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n451:     if addr == \"\" {\n452:         return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n453:     }\n454: \n455:     addresses := strings.Split(addr, \",\")\n456:     for i := range addresses {\n457:         addresses[i] = strings.TrimSpace(addresses[i])\n458:     }\n459: \n460:     password := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n461:     passwordRequired := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"))\n462:     if password == \"\" && passwordRequired != \"false\" {\n463:         return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required (set VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n464:     }\n465: \n466:     disableCache := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\")) == \"true\"\n467:     forceSingle := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\")) == \"true\"\n468: \n469:     client, err := valkey.NewClient(valkey.ClientOption{\n470:         InitAddress:       addresses,\n471:         Password:          password,\n472:         DisableCache:      disableCache,\n473:         ForceSingleClient: forceSingle,\n474:     })\n475:     if err != nil {\n476:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create valkey client: %w\", err)\n477:     }\n478: \n479:     return &valkeyStore{\n480:         cli:                  client,\n481:         sessionPrefix:        \"session:\",\n482:         expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\",\n483:         lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\",\n484:     }, nil\n485: }\n486: ```\n487: \n488: Note: Constructor does NOT perform a ping check. Connection validation occurs lazily on first operation.\n489: \n490: ---\n491: \n492: ## 4. Error Handling\n493: \n494: ### 4.1 Error Types\n495: \n496: | Error | Source | Handling |\n497: |-------|--------|----------|\n498: | `ErrNotFound` | Package sentinel (`store.go`) | Returned when session key absent |\n499: | `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` | valkey-go | Normalized to `ErrNotFound` in `GetSandbox` |\n500: | `DoMulti` result errors | Individual command errors | First error returned, batch aborts |\n501: | Validation errors | Input checks | Descriptive `errors.New()` messages |\n502: | Connection errors | Valkey client | Propagated with context |\n503: \n504: ### 4.2 Error Handling Matrix\n505: \n506: | Scenario | Error Returned | Notes |\n507: |----------|---------------|-------|\n508: | Session key not found | `ErrNotFound` | `valkey.IsValkeyNil` normalized |\n509: | Nil sandbox to StoreSandbox | `errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")` | Input validation |\n510: | Zero ExpiresAt | `errors.New(\"sandbox ExpiresAt is zero\")` | Input validation |\n511: | Empty sessionID | `errors.New(\"sessionID is empty\")` | UpdateSessionLastActivity |\n512: | UpdateSandbox missing key | `fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists: %s\", key)` | SET XX returns non-OK |\n513: | Missing VALKEY_ADDR | `errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")` | Constructor |\n514: | Missing VALKEY_PASSWORD | `errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required ...\")` | Unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n515: | Client creation failure | `fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create valkey client: %w\", err)` | Constructor |\n516: \n517: ### 4.3 Environment Variables\n518: \n519: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n520: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n521: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | — | Comma-separated addresses; split and trimmed |\n522: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes* | — | Auth password |\n523: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive `\"false\"` disables |\n524: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Case-insensitive `\"true\"` enables `DisableCache` |\n525: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Case-insensitive `\"true\"` enables `ForceSingleClient` |\n526: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Must be `valkey` for this backend |\n527: \n528: ---\n529: \n530: ## 5. Testing Strategy\n531: \n532: ### 5.1 Unit Test Matrix\n533: \n534: Valkey tests use mock `valkeyStore` structs (no in-memory Valkey server equivalent to miniredis). Tests cover validation logic, error paths, and structural correctness:\n535: \n536: | Test Name | Description | Assertions |\n537: |-----------|-------------|------------|\n538: | `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_NilInfo` | nil sandbox input | `assert.Contains(\"sandbox is nil\")` |\n539: | `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_ZeroExpiry` | Zero `ExpiresAt` | `assert.Contains(\"ExpiresAt is zero\")` |\n540: | `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_NilInfo` | nil sandbox input | `assert.Contains(\"sandbox is nil\")` |\n541: | `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_EmptySessionID` | Empty sessionID | `assert.Contains(\"sessionID is empty\")` |\n542: | `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_LimitZero` | limit=0 | Returns `nil, nil` |\n543: | `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_LimitNegative` | limit=-5 | Returns `nil, nil` |\n544: | `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes_LimitZero` | limit=0 | Returns `nil, nil` |\n545: | `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes_LimitNegative` | limit=-1 | Returns `nil, nil` |\n546: | `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_ZeroTime` | `at.IsZero()` logic | Verifies `time.Now()` substitution |\n547: | `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_ScoreCalculation` | Score for 1hr ago | `assert.Equal(int64(-3600))` |\n548: | `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes_ScoreCalculation` | Score for 2hr ago | `assert.Equal(int64(-7200))` |\n549: | `TestValkeyStore_StructFields` | Constant values | Field assertions |\n550: | `TestValkeyStore_InterfaceCompliance` | Compile-time check | `var _ Store = (*valkeyStore)(nil)` |\n551: | `TestNewValkeyStore_MissingAddr` | No `VALKEY_ADDR` | `assert.Contains(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")` |\n552: | `TestNewValkeyStore_MissingPassword` | No password, required | `assert.Contains(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required\")` |\n553: | `TestNewValkeyStore_PasswordNotRequired` | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | `require.NoError`, `require.NotNil` |\n554: | `TestNewValkeyStore_PasswordRequiredTrue` | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=true` | `assert.Contains(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required\")` |\n555: \n556: ### 5.2 Test Limitations\n557: \n558: Unlike the Redis tests which use `miniredis` for full integration testing, Valkey tests are limited to:\n559: - Input validation (nil checks, zero checks, empty checks)\n560: - Constructor environment variable parsing\n561: - Score calculation verification\n562: - Interface compliance compile-time checks\n563: - Struct field value assertions\n564: \n565: Full integration tests requiring a live Valkey server are not included.\n566: \n567: ### 5.3 Gate Requirements\n568: \n569: 1. `go build ./pkg/store/...` compiles\n570: 2. `go test ./pkg/store/... -v` all pass\n571: 3. `go test -race ./pkg/store/...` no data race warnings\n572: 4. No `log.Printf` usage (use klog)\n573: 5. No sensitive data in logs (passwords, connection strings)\n574: 6. Test coverage ≥ 80% for `store_valkey.go`\n575: \n576: ---\n577: \n578: ## 6. Deployment Considerations\n579: \n580: ### 6.1 Connection Pooling\n581: \n582: valkey-go manages its own connection pooling internally. Default settings should suffice for initial deployment. `ForceSingleClient` option available via `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true` for non-cluster setups.\n583: \n584: ### 6.2 Password Policy\n585: \n586: Password required by default. Set `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` only in trusted network environments.\n587: \n588: ### 6.3 ZSET Index Growth\n589: \n590: `session:expiry` and `session:last_activity` sorted sets grow monotonically. Ensure the GC controller regularly calls:\n591: - `ListExpiredSandboxes` → `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n592: - `ListInactiveSandboxes` → `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n593: \n594: ### 6.4 Memory Considerations\n595: \n596: - Session JSON strings: ~500 bytes per sandbox\n597: - ZSET entries: ~100 bytes per session ID per index\n598: - Estimated memory: ~700 bytes × number of active sessions\n599: \n600: ### 6.5 Valkey Cluster\n601: \n602: For Valkey Cluster deployments:\n603: - Consider hash tags for key slot affinity: `session:{cluster}:{sessionID}`\n604: - `ListSandboxes` iterates with individual GET calls (not MGET), avoiding CROSSSLOT issues\n605: - Monitor for cross-slot errors if future optimizations use MGET\n606: \n607: ### 6.6 Cache and Client Options\n608: \n609: - `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`: Disables client-side response caching\n610: - `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`: Forces single-client mode even with multiple addresses\n611: \n612: ---\n613: \n614: ## 7. Implementation Steps\n615: \n616: ### Phase 1: Core Implementation (Day 1)\n617: \n618: 1. Implement `valkeyStore` struct in `store_valkey.go`\n619: 2. Implement constructor with environment variable validation\n620: 3. Implement `Ping`, `Close`, `sessionKey` helper\n621: \n622: ### Phase 2: CRUD Operations (Day 2)\n623: \n624: 1. Implement `StoreSandbox` with `DoMulti`\n625: 2. Implement `UpdateSandbox` with SET XX\n626: 3. Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` with `DoMulti`\n627: 4. Implement `GetSandbox` with `ErrNotFound` handling\n628: \n629: ### Phase 3: Query Operations (Day 3)\n630: \n631: 1. Implement `ListSandboxes` with ZRANGE + individual GETs\n632: 2. Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes` with ZRANGEBYSCORE\n633: 3. Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes` with ZRANGEBYSCORE\n634: 4. Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity`\n635: \n636: ### Phase 4: Testing & Validation (Day 4)\n637: \n638: 1. Write unit tests (validation + constructor)\n639: 2. Run `go test -race ./pkg/store/...`\n640: 3. Verify test coverage\n641: 4. Fix all issues\n642: \n643: ---\n644: \n645: ## 8. Future Changes\n646: \n647: | Change | Description | Priority |\n648: |--------|-------------|----------|\n649: | AR-0XX | TTL on session keys for automatic cleanup | P1 |\n650: | AR-0XX | Hash tag support for Valkey Cluster slot affinity | P2 |\n651: | AR-0XX | Metrics: store operation latency, error rates | P2 |\n652: | AR-0XX | Integration tests with testcontainers-valkey | P2 |\n653: | AR-0XX | MGET optimization for batch loads (with hash tags) | P3 |\n654: \n655: ### Known Limitations\n656: \n657: - No automatic TTL on session JSON keys; relies on GC controller for cleanup\n658: - `ListSandboxes` and `List*` methods use individual GET calls instead of MGET; less efficient for large batches\n659: - No pagination for `List*` methods beyond simple `limit` parameter\n660: - `SETNX` in `StoreSandbox` prevents updates; use `UpdateSandbox` for modifications\n661: - No in-memory Valkey mock for integration testing; tests limited to validation logic\n662: - Constructor does not ping server; connection errors surface on first operation\n\n(End of file - total 662 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014 — Valkey Storage Implementation — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis document specifies the Valkey backend implementation for the `pkg/store` session storage module in AgentCube. It provides a concrete `Store` interface implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`, persisting sandbox metadata as JSON strings and maintaining sorted-set indices for garbage collection workflows.\n\n### 1.2 Valkey Data Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    valkeyStore                          │\n│  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  cli: valkey.Client                               │  │\n│  │  sessionPrefix:        \"session:\"                 │  │\n│  │  expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\"           │  │\n│  │  lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\"    │  │\n│  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────┘","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/design.md","time":{"start":1775838241699,"end":1775838241709}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775838243006,"sessionID":"ses_287cb09c2ffefSoaqLWDpvusWV","part":{"id":"prt_d783524320013XCySuiIZjE42u","messageID":"msg_d78350ea9001aSGzA3fc3lUbzn","sessionID":"ses_287cb09c2ffefSoaqLWDpvusWV","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_c982eb7ceb8846de9eda9e6e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 — Tasks\n2: \n3: > **Module:** pkg/store\n4: > **Language:** Go\n5: > **Size:** S\n6: > **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n7: > **Reference:** `changes/AR-014/design.md`, `changes/AR-014/proposal.md`, `delta-spec.md`\n8: \n9: ## T1. 实现 Valkey 构造函数\n10: \n11: - [ ] 1.1 创建 `store_valkey.go`，定义 `valkeyStore` 结构体（`cli valkey.Client`, `sessionPrefix`, `expiryIndexKey`, `lastActivityIndexKey`）\n12: - [ ] 1.2 实现 `newValkeyStore() (Store, error)` 构造函数\n13: - [ ] 1.3 验证 `VALKEY_ADDR` 非空，否则返回 `errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")`\n14: - [ ] 1.4 验证 `VALKEY_PASSWORD`（除非 `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`）\n15: - [ ] 1.5 支持 `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` 和 `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` 环境变量\n16: - [ ] 1.6 使用 `valkey.NewClient` 创建客户端（不执行 ping，连接惰性验证）\n17: - [ ] 1.7 更新 `singleton.go` 中 `initStore()` 支持 `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n18: - [ ] 1.8 新增构造函数单元测试 `TestNewValkeyStore_MissingAddr`\n19: - [ ] 1.9 新增构造函数单元测试 `TestNewValkeyStore_MissingPassword`\n20: - [ ] 1.10 新增构造函数单元测试 `TestNewValkeyStore_PasswordNotRequired`\n21: - [ ] 1.11 新增构造函数单元测试 `TestNewValkeyStore_PasswordRequiredTrue`\n22: \n23: **Verification:** `newValkeyStore` 签名返回 `(Store, error)`；无 `klog.Fatal` 调用；singleton.go 正确处理 error；构造测试全绿\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## T2. 实现 Valkey CRUD 操作\n28: \n29: - [ ] 2.1 实现 `sessionKey(sessionID string) string` 辅助方法（返回 `v.sessionPrefix + sessionID`）\n30: - [ ] 2.2 实现 `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` — `B().Ping().Build()` 校验 `\"PONG\"`\n31: - [ ] 2.3 实现 `GetSandbox(ctx, sessionID)` — `B().Get().Key(key).Build()`，`valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` → `ErrNotFound`\n32: - [ ] 2.4 实现 `StoreSandbox(ctx, sessionID, info)` — 验证 nil/零 ExpiresAt，`DoMulti`: SETNX + ZADD expiry + ZADD activity\n33: - [ ] 2.5 实现 `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sessionID, info)` — `B().Set().Key().Value().Xx().Build()`，响应非 `\"OK\"` 返回 `\"key not exists\"` 错误\n34: - [ ] 2.6 实现 `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` — `DoMulti`: DEL + ZREM expiry + ZREM activity\n35: - [ ] 2.7 实现 `Close() error` — 调用 `v.cli.Close()`\n36: - [ ] 2.8 运行 `go build ./pkg/store/...` 确认编译通过\n37: \n38: **Verification:** 所有方法签名与 `Store` 接口一致（design.md §3.1）；`go build` 零错误\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ## T3. 实现 Valkey 查询操作\n43: \n44: - [ ] 3.1 实现 `ListSandboxes(ctx)` — `ZRANGE` 0 -1 + 逐个 `GetSandbox`，跳过 `ErrNotFound`（孤儿 ZSET 成员容错），返回 `map[string]*types.SandboxInfo`\n45: - [ ] 3.2 实现 `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` — `limit <= 0` 返回 `nil, nil`；`ZRANGEBYSCORE` `-inf` 到 `before.Unix()` + 逐个 `GetSandbox`\n46: - [ ] 3.3 实现 `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` — 同 3.2，目标 key 为 `session:last_activity`\n47: - [ ] 3.4 实现 `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at)` — 空 sessionID 返回错误；零时间使用 `time.Now()`；`EXISTS` 验证 key 存在，不存在返回 `ErrNotFound`；`ZADD` 更新 activity score\n48: - [ ] 3.5 运行 `go build ./pkg/store/...` 确认编译通过\n49: \n50: **Verification:** 方法签名与 design.md §3.1 一致；List 方法使用逐个 GET 调用（非 MGET）；孤儿 ZSET 成员被跳过\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## T4. 编写 Valkey 单元测试\n55: \n56: - [ ] 4.1 创建 `store_valkey_test.go`\n57: - [ ] 4.2 编写 `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_NilInfo` — nil sandbox 输入返回 `\"sandbox is nil\"`\n58: - [ ] 4.3 编写 `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_ZeroExpiry` — 零 ExpiresAt 返回 `\"ExpiresAt is zero\"`\n59: - [ ] 4.4 编写 `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_NilInfo` — nil sandbox 输入返回 `\"sandbox is nil\"`\n60: - [ ] 4.5 编写 `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_EmptySessionID` — 空 sessionID 返回 `\"sessionID is empty\"`\n61: - [ ] 4.6 编写 `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_LimitZero` — limit=0 返回 `nil, nil`\n62: - [ ] 4.7 编写 `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_LimitNegative` — limit=-5 返回 `nil, nil`\n63: - [ ] 4.8 编写 `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes_LimitZero` — limit=0 返回 `nil, nil`\n64: - [ ] 4.9 编写 `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes_LimitNegative` — limit=-1 返回 `nil, nil`\n65: - [ ] 4.10 编写 `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_ZeroTime` — 零时间使用 `time.Now()` 替代\n66: - [ ] 4.11 编写 `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_ScoreCalculation` — 1 小时前 score = -3600\n67: - [ ] 4.12 编写 `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes_ScoreCalculation` — 2 小时前 score = -7200\n68: - [ ] 4.13 编写 `TestValkeyStore_StructFields` — 常量值断言\n69: - [ ] 4.14 编写 `TestValkeyStore_InterfaceCompliance` — 编译期 `var _ Store = (*valkeyStore)(nil)`\n70: - [ ] 4.15 运行 `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -count=1` 全部通过\n71: \n72: **Verification:** 测试覆盖 design.md §5.1 测试矩阵全部用例；`go test -cover ./pkg/store/...` 覆盖率 ≥ 80%\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## T5. 竞态检测与门禁验证\n77: \n78: - [ ] 5.1 运行 `go test -race ./pkg/store/...` 无 data race 警告\n79: - [ ] 5.2 确认无 `log.Printf` 使用（仅允许 `klog`）\n80: - [ ] 5.3 确认日志中无敏感数据（密码、连接字符串）\n81: - [ ] 5.4 运行 `go vet ./pkg/store/...` 无警告\n82: - [ ] 5.5 运行 `go mod tidy` 确保依赖正确\n83: - [ ] 5.6 确认 `go build ./pkg/store/...` 编译通过\n84: \n85: **Verification:** 以上 6 项全部通过\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: ## Task Dependencies\n90: \n91: ```\n92: T1 ──→ T2 ──→ T3 ──→ T4 ──→ T5\n93: ```\n94: \n95: ## Acceptance Criteria\n96: \n97: | # | Criterion | Command |\n98: |---|-----------|---------|\n99: | AC1 | 编译通过 | `go build ./pkg/store/...` |\n100: | AC2 | 全部测试通过 | `go test ./pkg/store/... -v -count=1` |\n101: | AC3 | 无竞态条件 | `go test -race ./pkg/store/...` |\n102: | AC4 | 覆盖率 ≥ 80% | `go test -cover ./pkg/store/...` |\n103: | AC5 | 无 lint 警告 | `go vet ./pkg/store/...` |\n104: | AC6 | Store 接口 10 个方法全部实现 | `var _ Store = (*valkeyStore)(nil)` 编译通过 |\n105: | AC7 | List 方法使用逐个 GET 调用（非 MGET） | 代码审查 |\n106: | AC8 | `StoreSandbox` 拒绝零 ExpiresAt | `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_ZeroExpiry` 通过 |\n107: | AC9 | 构造函数返回 error 而非 klog.Fatal | 代码审查 + 单元测试 |\n108: | AC10 | `STORE_TYPE=valkey` 时 singleton 选择 Valkey 后端 | 代码审查 |\n109: | AC11 | 孤儿 ZSET 成员在 List 方法中被跳过 | 代码审查 |\n\n(End of file - total 109 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** pkg/store\n> **Language:** Go\n> **Size:** S\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-014/design.md`, `changes/AR-014/proposal.md`, `delta-spec.md`\n\n## T1. 实现 Valkey 构造函数\n\n- [ ] 1.1 创建 `store_valkey.go`，定义 `valkeyStore` 结构体（`cli valkey.Client`, `sessionPrefix`, `expiryIndexKey`, `lastActivityIndexKey`）\n- [ ] 1.2 实现 `newValkeyStore() (Store, error)` 构造函数\n- [ ] 1.3 验证 `VALKEY_ADDR` 非空，否则返回 `errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")`\n- [ ] 1.4 验证 `VALKEY_PASSWORD`（除非 `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`）\n- [ ] 1.5 支持 `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` 和 `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` 环境变量\n- [ ] 1.6 使用 `valkey.NewClient` 创建客户端（不执行 ping，连接惰性验证）\n- [ ] 1.7 更新 `singleton.go` 中 `initStore()` 支持 `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n- [ ] 1.8 新增构造函数单元测试 `TestNewValkeyStore_MissingAddr`\n- [ ] 1.9 新增构造函数单元测试 `TestNewValkeyStore_MissingPassword`\n- [ ] 1.10 新增构造函数单元测试 `TestNewValkeyStore_PasswordNotRequired`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775838242997,"end":1775838243004}}}}
